B.Uw=new A.jH("5","The Blueprint for a Good Night's Sleep","General Wellness","3 min read","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1511295742364-92767fa62d9f?w=1200&q=90","Sleep is the foundation of health. During deep sleep, your body repairs tissues, synthesizes proteins, and consolidates memory. To improve sleep hygiene: establish a consistent sleep schedule, make your bedroom dark and cool, avoid screen time for at least 1 hour before bed, and limit heavy meals or caffeine in the evening. Aim for 7 to 9 hours of quality sleep nightly.")
B.Ux=new A.jH("3","Top 5 Cardio Exercises to Do at Home","Exercise Tips","2 min read","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1517838277536-f5f99be501cd?w=1200&q=90","No gym membership? No problem! You can easily maintain your fitness levels at home. Jump jacks, high knees, mountain climbers, burpees, and shadow boxing are excellent bodyweight cardiovascular exercises. Performing these in a high-intensity interval training (HIIT) circuit of 20 minutes a day boosts cardiovascular endurance, burns calories, and improves metabolic rate.")
B.Uy=new A.jH("2","Mindfulness Practices for Stress Relief","Mental Wellbeing","3 min read","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506126613408-eca07ce68773?w=1200&q=90","In today's fast-paced world, stress is common. Practicing mindfulness, even for five minutes a day, can lower cortisol levels, reduce anxiety, and improve emotional health. Try deep breathing exercises: inhale for 4 seconds, hold for 4, exhale for 4, and hold for 4. Regular meditation helps retrain your brain to respond calmly to stressful events.")
B.Uz=new A.jH("4","Boosting Your Immune System in Winter","Seasonal Health","2 min read","https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1511688868355-7216e2161561?w=1200&q=90","Cold temperatures often lead to indoor crowding, increasing viral spread. Boost your immune defense by prioritizing sleep, staying physically active, and eating foods rich in Vitamin C, D, and Zinc. Citrus fruits, leafy greens, ginger tea, and fermented foods like yogurt provide vital nutrients. Don't forget to wash hands regularly and sanitize frequently touched objects.")
B.UA=new A.jH("1","Hydration 101: Why Water Matters","Nutrition","2 min read",u.P,"Water is essential for every cell, tissue, and organ in your body. It helps regulate temperature, lubricate joints, and carry nutrients to your cells. Aim for at least 8-10 glasses of water daily to stay energized, improve skin health, and support kidney function. Carrying a reusable water bottle can remind you to sip throughout the day.")
